/ ''heru usage claude'' / ''heru usage copilot'' / ''heru\n  usage zai'' each prints usage for that single provider'\n- '''heru usage gemini'' prints an ''unsupported'' notice rather than crashing'\n- '''heru usage <unknown>'' prints a helpful error listing valid provider names and\n  exits non-zero'\n- Output includes used, limit, remaining, unit, reset window, and active block_reason\n  if any\n- --json flag emits machine-readable output (one JSON object per provider, or a single\n  object for the single-provider form)\n- Missing auth / missing credential file is reported per-provider, not as a crash\n- \"Fixture-driven tests under tests/ cover success, unsupported, unknown-name, missing-auth,\\\n  \\ and --json paths \\u2014 zero real network calls\"\n- README documents 'heru usage' and 'heru usage <name>'\n- heru/quota/ module name is unchanged (internal naming stays consistent with provider\n  APIs)\n- uv run pytest tests/ passes\n- litehive contract tests from ~/git/litehive still pass\nconstraints:\n- Keep provider-specific behavior isolated to the adapter boundary.\n- Preserve deterministic workspace state and execution flow.\nplan:\n- Inspect the existing adapter interface, config wiring, and invocation flow.\n- Implement the adapter change close to the integration seam.\n- Verify the adapter path with a focused test or representative run.\nhuman_checkpoints: []\nsubagents:\n- id: SA-0001\n  role: planner\n  engine: codex\n  status: completed\n  path: subagents/SA-0001-planner\n  sandboxed: false\n  sandbox_summary: host\n- id: SA-0002\n  role: swe\n  engine: codex\n  status: completed\n  path: subagents/SA-0002-swe\n  sandboxed: false\n  sandbox_summary: host\n- id: SA-0003\n  role: qa\n  engine: codex\n  status: completed\n  path: subagents/SA-0003-qa\n  sandboxed: false\n  sandbox_summary: host\n- id: SA-0004\n  role: reviewer\n  engine: codex\n  status: completed\n  path: subagents/SA-0004-reviewer\n  sandboxed: false\n  sandbox_summary: host\ngit:\n  a